column5: Seems it's still pretty hard. So I managed to get out to my cabin property with another load of materials.  Even my GPS knows I'm driving on ice. How does it know?    The lake was in pretty good condition with only a couple of sketchy areas.    For those of you you think Honda's are only good for taking the kids to soccer practice and picking up groceries, they are pretty capable with decent tires and the center locking differential engaged. She walked right up the rocks no problem.
Awesome... Cept fer the honda part
Awesome... Cept fer the honda part  Last time I was in Alaska I pulled out a stuck suburban on the beach.
How thick do you think the ice is?  Wonder how long before ice out up there!!
2 weeks ago it was about 5 1/2 feet!!!  Here's a pic of my buddy out fishin' then.    Still has to be 4 feet I would think.
2 weeks ago it was about 5 1/2 feet!!!  Here's a pic of my buddy out fishin' then.    Still has to be 4 feet I would think.  straight up... I couldnt imagine
Let the adventure begin!!!Love those auger extensions.May and you still need 5' to get thru.lol. Do you think you will get most of your materials in before ice melt?

Just when I begin to envy your awesome outdoor situation I remember OH yeah the winters bbrrrrrhhhhh. Your going to have a great time building and using that cabin. Just hope you don't John Hornby the whole thing.

Do you think you will get most of your materials in before ice melt?  Nope. Still waiting on delivery of my dock hardware and floats and won't  be ordering subflooring and other materials to do the foundation and 1st floor deck until summer.  Just hope you don't John Hornby the whole thing.
Here's another good shot. My buddy setting his net a few days ago. He is still standing on 2 feet of ice!!!!
